      "message": "No need to mix normal quotes (first line of help) and docstring quotes (rest of help).\nYou can achieve multiline help in 2 ways:\n\na) Use docstring all the way to avoid manual \"\\n\" line breaks. Downside is that text in docstring has to be all the way to the left side, no indentation.\n\n```\nparser.add_argument(\u0027-method\u0027, dest\u003d\u0027method\u0027, default\u003dNone,\n                    help\u003d\"\"\"test\naaa\nbbb\"\"\")\n```\n\n\nb) Using single quotes:\n\n```\nparser.add_argument(\u0027-method\u0027, dest\u003d\u0027method\u0027, default\u003dNone,\n                    help\u003d\"aaa:\\n\"\n                         \"bbb\\n\n                         \"ccc.\")\n\n```",
